  "caption": "Anthropic launched the strongest cybersecurity model it has ever built on June 9, then pointed it at the defenders instead of the open market.\n\nThe public model, Fable 5, has its offensive edge gated. The full-power version, Mythos 5, goes only to vetted cyberdefenders and the US government through a program called Project Glasswing. On a live exploit benchmark it scores 78 percent, where today's strongest public model sits at 40. That is a real jump in finding and chaining vulnerabilities.\n\nFor once the sharpest capability is reaching defense first. You probably will not get Mythos, so plan for the capability, not the access: assume attackers reach parity eventually and shorten your patch window now, because patch velocity is the control that scales with this.\n\nAnd read the fine print. Mythos-class traffic now carries a mandatory 30-day retention, even where you had a zero-retention agreement before. Re-check what your team is allowed to send these models.\n\nDoes your patch window survive an attacker with a model like this?\n\nFollow for AI security breakdowns without the fake panic.\n\n[Mythos 5, Claude Fable 5, Anthropic, Project Glasswing, defensive AI, patch velocity, data retention]",
